BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260508T061200
DTEND:20260508T161200
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.602ft at 06:12\n-2.972ft at 16:12\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 <strong>Dawn to 10:00AM:</strong> Easing blend of SSW and WNW swell for wa
 ves mainly running thigh-waist high+. Light/variable winds through the mor
 ning. Incoming tide push mid day gets an assist. \n\n<strong>Afternoon Out
 look:</strong> Wave size holds. Gentle S sea breeze for some afternoon tex
 ture. Later afternoon high tide slows tide sensitive breaks. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260509T063600
DTEND:20260509T163000
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.938ft at 06:36\n-2.969ft at 16:30\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Mainly old swell for thigh-waist high surf in the morning\, then some new 
 WNW/NW swell and SSW Southern Hemi joins in during the afternoon\, for mor
 e waist-stomach high waves. \n\nLight/variable winds due all day for at le
 ast semi-clean conditions. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260510T072400
DTEND:20260510T164200
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.996ft at 07:24\n-2.97ft at 16:42\n\nOBSERVATION:\nN
 ice combo of long-period SSW Southern Hemi and shorter-period NW/WNW swell
  mix rolling in\, setting up widespread waist-chest high waves\, as summer
 time focal points go head high. Afternoon sees most size. \n\nLight/variab
 le winds through the morning\, turning light S onshore for the afternoon. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260511T082400
DTEND:20260511T164800
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.976ft at 08:24\n-2.926ft at 16:48\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Long-period SSW Southern Hemi peaks\, while and shorter-period NW/WNW swel
 l mix holds\, maintaining waist-chest high waves\, as summertime standouts
  are head high+. \n\nPattern of light/variable winds through the morning\,
  followed by light+ SW afternoon onshores expected to persist. 
END:VEVENT
